full_text: Screened by NARA, 9/21/2023 NITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE IMMIGRATION AND NATURALIZATION SERVICE Officer litt. Processing Sheet Application or Date 5/26/78 Petition Form No. I-485-C File No A21 235-980 6 IR6 #3 NAME. Family name (in caps) followed by given name and middle name Ngoc MAU thi 1 RAN DOB: ENTRY: Same Paroled as I-94 Refugee you Change verified Admitted by Affidavit NIV or B/C as as on or before 3/31/75 PRESENCE: Meets 2-year physical presence requirement MEDICAL: Not required (Paroled through you Refugee camp) Pendilton (needs not be continuous) Must be obtained G-325-A and fingerprints LOCAL POLICE CHECKS: Must be yes (not required if under 14) obtained from each location of residence in the U.S. of Face (not required if under 14) 6 months or more none requested PHOTOS: yes ADIT PROCESSING CARD: gis CLASSIFICATION: (circle one) Supplemental Sheet: agos IC6 Native or Citizen of Vietnam, Laos, or Cambodia IC7 Non-native or non-citizen of above countries but who is the spouse or child of above. (This class must also meet the entry and 2-year physical presence requirements.) IC8 Previously adjusted native or citizen of Vietnam, Laos, or Cambodia who is applying for rollback date of permanent residence IC9 Previously adjusted applicant who is neither a native or citizen of Vietnam, Laos, or Cambodia, but who is the spouse or child of Indochina refugee and is applying for a rollback date of permanent residence. Form I-181 G-601 OK to Grant Except for 1. 2. 3. This form may be overprinted or stamped to show instructions, items requested, items received, or other pertinent data which may facilitate processing. Keep this sheet on top of all material in file until initial decision is made Form I-468 (Rev. 11-1-70)
